1
00:00:05,384 --> 00:00:07,019
What is Kṛṣṇa telling Arjuna?

2
00:00:07,019 --> 00:00:13,081
Earth, water, fire, air, ether,
mind, intelligence, ego …

3
00:00:13,081 --> 00:00:15,985
these are My energy.

4
00:00:16,077 --> 00:00:19,622
They’re My separated diverse energies
of a lower quality.

5
00:00:20,022 --> 00:00:23,382
[The Central Conception of the Infinite]

6
00:00:23,659 --> 00:00:26,735
But Arjuna, there’s another energy
higher than this:

7
00:00:26,890 --> 00:00:32,051
the jīva-śakti,
and it’s driving the universe.

8
00:00:32,268 --> 00:00:35,998
It’s the power. 
They’re all over the place.

9
00:00:36,198 --> 00:00:39,835
Once, Prabhupād was saying,
“There are many meanings of Kṛṣṇa.

10
00:00:40,020 --> 00:00:42,634
One meaning of Kṛṣṇa is ‘wandering’.”

11
00:00:42,727 --> 00:00:46,463
So, he said, “The jivas are Kṛṣṇa,

12
00:00:47,201 --> 00:00:51,338
they’re wandering
throughout the universe.”

13
00:00:51,953 --> 00:00:55,853
So, Kṛṣṇa’s also saying,
“They’re My aṁśa.”

14
00:00:56,506 --> 00:01:00,137
They’re like—what does it say
in Daśa-Mūla, Bhakti Vinod?

15
00:01:00,191 --> 00:01:04,138
Bhedābhed,
they’re the same and different.

16
00:01:04,138 --> 00:01:06,404
Same same, but different.

17
00:01:07,173 --> 00:01:12,068
So, if we make the mistake
of seeing things as separate from Kṛṣṇa,

18
00:01:12,091 --> 00:01:13,815
that is not good.

19
00:01:13,845 --> 00:01:18,910
That’s actually part of the cause
of our predicament,

20
00:01:18,910 --> 00:01:23,212
not seeing things related to Kṛṣṇa
—what to speak of avatar.

21
00:01:23,212 --> 00:01:28,115
If we can see how energy
and mundane things …

22
00:01:28,115 --> 00:01:32,138
we can trace their position back
to the central conception of the Infinite.

